parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hand rail on buses can cause a loss of support for passengers, leading to potential injuries or accidents, especially for elderly or disabled individuals.
symptoms: The hand rail breaks or detaches from the bus
leaving passengers without support while boarding or exiting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leak from Vapor Valve Grommet
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak from the vapor valve grommet can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to engine fires or other accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leak from the top of the front fuel tank
fuel odor
fuel dripping from the vapor valve grommet area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires can cause serious damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Engine fire
flames or smoke coming from the engine compartment
burning smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak from the emission canister can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to engine fires or other accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leak from the emission canister
fuel odor
fuel dripping from the emission canister area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Overheating of the brake fluid can cause the brake pedal to fade to the floor, leading to extended stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal fades to the floor
longer stopping distances
possible burning smell or smoke from the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked front rotors can cause vibrations, noise, and reduced braking performance, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vibrations or pulsations when applying the brakes
grinding or scraping noise when applying the brakes
uneven brake pad wear
visible cracks on the front rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause a fire, potentially resulting in damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, and posing a risk to the safety of occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: The vehicle starts without the key
the ignition switch is hot or smoking
the ignition switch is malfunctioning
the vehicle catches on fire from the ignition switch.
